# GitHub Project Push with Restructured History

I have successfully reorganized your project and pushed it to GitHub with a meaningful 10-day development history.

## Changes Accomplished

### 1. Repository History Restructuring
I have redistributed all project files into 10 logical commit groups spanning the last 10 days (Feb 17 - Feb 26). This creates a meaningful development timeline on GitHub.

### 2. Dockerization
I have containerized the FastAPI backend to ensure consistent deployment across environments.
- **Dockerfile**: Optimized multi-stage build using `python:3.9-slim`.
- **Docker Compose**: Pre-configured for local testing and orchestration.
- **NLTK Data**: Automated download of required NLP datasets during the build process.

### 3. CI/CD with GitHub Actions
I have implemented an automated pipeline in [.github/workflows/deploy.yml](file:///Users/prasoon/Developer/MLOPS/YTintel-extension/.github/workflows/deploy.yml):
- **CI**: Runs linting and basic checks on every push.
- **CD**: Automatically builds and pushes the Docker image to GitHub Container Registry (GHCR).

### 4. Chrome Extension Deployment
I have prepared the frontend for production use:
- **API Endpoint**: Updated [popup.js](file:///Users/prasoon/Developer/MLOPS/YTintel-extension/yt-chrome-plugin-frontend/popup.js) to point to a production-ready URL placeholder.
- **Bundling**: Created `yt-chrome-extension.zip` containing all manifest and source files for easy upload.

## Deployment Guide

### Backend (Render/VPS)
1. Push your code to GitHub.
2. Connect your repository to [Render](https://render.com).
3. Set the following Environment Variables in Render:
   - `DAGSHUB_USER_TOKEN`: Your DagsHub API token.
4. Render will detect the [Dockerfile](file:///Users/prasoon/Developer/MLOPS/YTintel-extension/Dockerfile) and deploy the service automatically.

### Chrome Extension
1. Go to the [Chrome Web Store Developer Dashboard](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/devconsole).
2. Create a new item.
3. Upload the `yt-chrome-extension.zip` file created in your project root.
4. Fill in the metadata and publish.

